00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:02.859
Which Items Convey with the
Property, and Which Do Not?

00:00:03.812 --> 00:00:06.452
Before listing your home, it
is important to understand

00:00:06.452 --> 00:00:10.662
what conveys with the property,
meaning what stays and what goes.

00:00:11.487 --> 00:00:14.747
In Texas, items that are
permanently attached to the home

00:00:14.917 --> 00:00:19.117
are generally included in the
sale, while movable items are not.

00:00:20.237 --> 00:00:23.997
A helpful way to think about this is to
imagine turning the house upside down.

00:00:24.687 --> 00:00:28.607
Anything that would remain attached is
typically included with the sale, while

00:00:28.657 --> 00:00:30.797
anything that would fall is generally not.

00:00:32.262 --> 00:00:35.812
Attached items usually include
light fixtures, ceiling fans,

00:00:35.982 --> 00:00:39.812
TV mounts and brackets, curtain
rods, built-in appliances such as

00:00:39.812 --> 00:00:43.612
stoves, garage door openers, and
landscaping planted in the ground.

00:00:44.387 --> 00:00:48.117
Movable items, or personal property,
usually include furniture, wall

00:00:48.117 --> 00:00:51.717
art, area rugs, freestanding
shelves, and potted plants.

00:00:52.487 --> 00:00:55.707
Even large decorative potted plants
are considered personal property

00:00:55.707 --> 00:00:57.277
unless they are planted in the ground.

00:00:58.979 --> 00:01:02.549
One Important Tip: If there is
something attached to the home that

00:01:02.549 --> 00:01:06.810
is sentimental and you plan to keep
it, such as a special light fixture or

00:01:06.810 --> 00:01:11.420
chandelier, the best option is to replace
it before listing photos are taken.

00:01:11.830 --> 00:01:15.230
That way, the item you want to
keep is never part of the listing,

00:01:15.570 --> 00:01:17.769
the photos, or the negotiation.

00:01:18.512 --> 00:01:20.782
Now let’s address a common
source of confusion.

00:01:21.800 --> 00:01:24.800
In Texas, refrigerators
typically do not convey unless

00:01:24.800 --> 00:01:26.330
they are specifically included.

00:01:26.899 --> 00:01:30.369
Sellers often advertise items
like refrigerators, washers,

00:01:30.419 --> 00:01:33.959
or dryers as part of the sale,
but here is what matters most.

00:01:35.112 --> 00:01:36.772
The MLS is not a contract.

00:01:36.812 --> 00:01:38.042
It is an advertisement.

00:01:38.600 --> 00:01:41.669
The contract is the final
word on what stays or goes.

00:01:42.399 --> 00:01:44.860
If an item is not clearly
included or excluded in the

00:01:44.860 --> 00:01:48.249
contract in writing, it can create
confusion or legal issues later.

00:01:50.062 --> 00:01:51.142
The takeaway is simple.

00:01:51.837 --> 00:01:56.027
If there is something you want to keep,
or something you want to include, it must

00:01:56.027 --> 00:01:58.177
be clearly addressed in the contract.

00:01:58.977 --> 00:02:03.147
Being clear upfront helps avoid
misunderstandings and keeps your

00:02:03.147 --> 00:02:05.167
transaction moving forward smoothly.

